1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4
{ The Bishop is on the most aggressive square and pressures f7. } 3... Bc5
{ This move is played most often. } 4. O-O Nf6 5. d4
{ We don't play d3! This is a real forcing move, which gives us the initiative. }
5... Nxd4
{ Even this natural move falls into a trap. I had this position often in blitz games. }
6. Nxe5 Ne6 { This is a try to limit the damage. } 7. Bxe6 fxe6 8. Nd3 Bb6 9.
e5 { White is won. This opening is so dangerous ! } 9... Ng8 10. Qg4
{ Let's take a look and see how Black loses because of his inferior development. }
10... Qe7 11. c4 { With the threat of c5. } 11... d6 12. Nc3 Bd7 13. Bg5 Qf7
14. exd6 cxd6 15. c5 { The final tactic ! } 15... Bxc5 16. Nxc5 dxc5 17. Ne4
{ My engine gives +3 for White because of space, development, better pieces, and Black's weaknesses. }
