1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4
{ The Bishop is on the most aggressive square and pressures f7. } 3... Bc5
{ This move is played most often. } 4. O-O Nf6 5. d4
{ We don't play d3! This is a real forcing move, which gives us the initiative. }
5... exd4
{ This natural move means a very uncomfortable game for the black player. White's initiative is just stunning! }
6. e5 Ng4
{ This is an inaccuracy, but it's very important that you understand the right way to benefit from it.  Many weaker players play this move after which we will have a much easier game. }
7. Bf4 d6 { Seems dangerous due to the opened king. } 8. exd6 Bxd6 9. Re1+ Be7
10. c3
{ This is our standard pawn-break. We won't regain the pawn at first, but our initiative is big enough to give us a clear advantage. }
10... dxc3 11. Nxc3 Qxd1 12. Raxd1 { And c7 is falling. } *

