1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4
{ The Bishop is on the most aggressive square and pressures f7. } 3... Bc5
{ This move is played most often. } 4. O-O Nf6 5. d4
{ We don't play d3! This is a real forcing move, which gives us the initiative. }
5... Bxd4
{ This is the best move, if Black knows what to do, he will equalize but it won't be easy at all, White will obtain the initiative for a long time and its very hard for a non-titled player to survive against a prepared Max Lange Gambit player. Usually we will always regain our pawn. }
6. Nxd4 Nxd4 7. Bg5
{ The main move is  7.f4  , but this tricky move leaves the common theory and is full of tricks. You have to know that the position is objectively about equal, but Black has to know what to do. }
7... d6 { This is the best move. } 8. f4
{ This is our standard break which saves us the initiative. Usually we will regain the sacrificed pawn. }
8... Bg4
{ This is a very rare try  (in the Power Book 2019 there is only one game)  but it's very important for us to know how to play against it. The 8... Bg4 line seems to bring good equalizing chances but we will be prepared against it in detail and will make life hard for Black. }
9. Bxf6 { That's the right move, we have to force the exchange of the queens. }
9... Bxd1 10. Bxd8 Rxd8
{ Black has to take on d8, if he doesn't, he will be down in material. } 11. c3
{ This is the best move. After  11.Rxd1  Nxc2  we would give Black better chances. }
11... Nc2 { This looks natural but gives us good chances to play for win. } 12.
Rxd1 Nxa1 13. Na3 { The black knight is captured. } 13... exf4
{ If Black doesn't take on f4, he will just have a rook and a pawn for two minor pieces which is too little. }
14. Rxa1 O-O 15. Kf2
{ That's why we have an advantage. Our king will be activated quickly and as the result we will pressure Black's weaknesses most effectively. }
15... Rfe8 16. Kf3 g5 { Take a look at Black's vulnerable pawn structure. } 17.
h4 h6 { Taking on h4 was no serious option. } 18. Nb5
{ Our strong knight is heading for f5. Our two pieces are much stronger than Black's rook and the two pawns  (he will probabily lose one soon)  . }
